HEADWORD: Indeficient
<hw>In`de*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indeficiens</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Deficient</er>.]</ety> <def>Not deficient; full.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brighter than the sun, and <qex>indeficient</qex> as the light of
heaven.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indefinable</ent>⟦br⟧
